---
title: "Secuencia — Subida Segura con Hash SHA-256 (FSD-UC-002)"
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor E as Estudiante
    participant SPA as React SPA
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant FS as file-service
    participant CB as CB[S3]
    participant S3 as MinIO/S3
    participant BD as PostgreSQL
    participant OB as Outbox Table
    participant SQS as AWS SQS
    participant NS as notification-service

    E->>SPA: Arrastra archivo (2GB)
    SPA->>GW: POST /drops/:id/upload/init (JWT)
    GW->>GW: Valida JWT
    GW->>FS: Inicia sesión de upload
    FS->>BD: INSERT upload_session {uploadId, chunks, progress=0%}
    FS-->>SPA: {uploadId, presignedUrls[]}

    loop Por cada chunk (8MB)
        SPA->>S3: PUT chunk (presigned URL directa)
        S3-->>SPA: 200 OK
        SPA->>GW: PATCH /upload/:id/progress
        GW->>FS: Actualiza progreso
        FS->>CB: Check CircuitBreaker[S3]
        CB-->>FS: CLOSED
        FS->>BD: UPDATE upload_session progress%
        FS-->>SPA: {progress: N%, speed: "X MB/s"}
    end

    SPA->>GW: POST /upload/:id/complete
    GW->>FS: CompleteMultipartUpload
    FS->>S3: CompleteMultipartUpload API
    S3-->>FS: 200 OK (ETag final)
    FS->>FS: Calcula SHA-256 del stream final

    Note over FS,OB: Transacción atómica PostgreSQL
    FS->>BD: INSERT archivo {hash, solo_lectura=true}
    FS->>OB: INSERT FileUploadedEvent {fileId, docenteId, hash}
    BD-->>FS: COMMIT

    FS-->>SPA: {fileId, hash_sha256, recibo_url}
    SPA-->>E: ✅ Entrega confirmada + Recibo PDF

    Note over OB,NS: Async — Message Relay
    OB->>SQS: Publica FileUploadedEvent
    SQS->>NS: Consume evento
    NS-->>E: Email/Push al docente "Nueva entrega"
